description: Spider-Man and the X-Men must douse the flames of a leadership squabble within the Hellfire Club. But why is J. Jonah Jameson to blame?
name: Double or Nothing
"...What If The Hulk got himself cured?"

description: At last! Professor Xavier confronts Nate Grey. Find out what happens when the two most powerful minds on earth collide in a psychic battle for the ages.
name: Confrontation

description: Reprints from The Mighty World of Marvel #7-10
name: The Candlelight Dialogue

description: The X-Men face off against a mutant vampire!
name: Horse Latitudes
The Homecoming, Part One: Journey to the East

description:
A man with a striking resemblance to Magneto stumbles into an orphanage. His name is Joseph and he possesses the uncanny ability to control metal. Who is this strange amnesiac?

Joseph makes his first full appearance after his cameo in X-men 46 (11-1995). He wakes up in a church and is sent out to find the X-Men.
name: Whispers On the Wind

description:
Aquaman discovers what's been raising Atlantis: an alien ship guarded by the dragon-like Tiamat, an ancient god. To defeat it, Aquaman must become one with the ship as the whole city breaks the surface of the water, creating tidal waves throughout the globe!

As Aquaman, Mera, Dolphin, and A.J. stare at Attlan's face through the viewing device, Aquaman is able to convince he father to rescue them, making a portal to draw them through. However upon arrival in the dimension, A.J. begins aging rapidly due to his being born in the Netherspace causing Mera to throw him back through as well as herself with Aquaman failing to stop her, much to his horror. Aquaman then realizes where Atlan has transported them to the sentient area underneath Poseidonis. While Aquaman realizes this place holds many answers Posiedonis once again begins to rise, while in the same area a monster realizes this to be Atlan's doing. The creature Tiamat then scoffs at Aquaman's assertion that his dreams have prepared him to come to this place, before leaping into battle, until Tiamut's very ship turns against it as it had long learned a love for humanity. The ship ultimately fulfills a ancient prophecy when it raises the very dome of Poseidonis above the ocean.

Meanwhile Admiral Strom has shown the threat Thanatos recorded prior to his death to several other top ranking military officials .While in the sacred tunnels where they come along an ancient casing of shells and seaweed which confounds even Vulko himself. Ultimately the casing is revealed to contain Kordax himself,who vows to rule the world.
name: Chronicles

description: Logan and his fellow X-Men go camping! Stories are swapped round the campfire, and Wolverine reflects on past heartache. Cyber finds himself at the wrong end of a feeding frenzy!
name: Campfire Tales

description: Cable and Domino land back in the present but not anywhere near where they expected. They are in Genosha, a country bent on reform in one way or another. The rebel forces are about to discover the island's secrets thanks to help from Mr. Sinister. Both the Sugar Man and the old magistrates plan to take out the rebels. Problem: Cable has joined them.
name: The Long Way Home
Luthor: Back in Charge!
Family Values

description: Psychos, thugs, and murderers. They've come to his town to take a piece of what little is left, unwanted guests at an inopportune time. X has chased the Feds out of Arcadia, leaving him to deal with the havoc alone. But that's okay... he has his own special way off handling unwanted guests.
name: Big Stars!

description: Luse explain to Cassy his history with Lester and gets a little payback. Luse also gets a bump to the head and we have the return of an old friend.
name: Sanctuary Book 2: Vivisettion One: Lester

description: Crash-landing in the dangerous jungles of Amazonia, Catwoman begins a desperate search for a former Nazi--possibly the only person alive who can free her from servitude.
name: Groddspell

description: Kahvi challenges Two-Spear for her right to be Go-Backs inside of a dreary cave. Kahvi steals Egg's egg.
name: MUSIC OF THE SPEARS

description:
Two Spear has his maddening vision of the humans' way of life. He emerges as an insensitive and ruthless murderer who begins to vanquish all people from the forest. An orphan boy witnesses the murdering of his mother by Two-Spear's hand.

Two-Spear returns to the Wolfriders in order to call council and announce plans for a war of racial extinction. But Huntress Skyfire has already found and adopted the orphan. In the council she pleads on behalf of the tribe, claiming that her brother is insane. She challenges him for the right to be wolfrider chief.
name: CHALLENGE

description: Dangerously immersed in the political intrigues of Egypt, Vincent's latest incarnation battles the power of the Priests...and finds help and much more from an unexpected source.
name: The Book of the Angel

description: Jealous of Leonardo and Isabella's budding relationship, Salai schemes to turn the two against one another, with poor Katherine as the unwitting pawn. Meanwhile, a longtime stranger returns to Isabella's household, and the origin of the Mona Lisa is revealed.

name: Falls Upon Wayne Manor: Anatomy of a Murder

description: Nightwing escapes back to Gotham, while learning his parents' true connection to the Prince.
name: Dead Simple

description: Enchantress appearance. Loki cameo. Thor gets a new costume. Curzon search a trach of Thor and investegated with L.t Stone
name: World Engine - Run Down
The Subterraneans, Part 3

description:
"The Trial of Superman" part 5, continued from Action Comics (1938-2011) #716. Superman and the two remaining fugitives meet Freelance, who has been sent by the Tribunal to retrieve them. Continued in Superman (1987-2006) #107.

Superman is wanted and a rowdy crew of space pirates are trying to collect the reward. The captain, Freelance, challenges Superman to a duel, with a wager: Freelance wins, they get to bring Superman to the Tribunals, but if Big Blue wins, he and his friends go free. Meanwhile, Team Superman is being ambushed. Finally, they all escape, only to engage in a climactic final scene.
name: Sky Pirates!

description:
An UNDERWORLD UNLEASHED tie-in issue! XS becomes trapped in the 20th century and is discovered by a Neron-empowered Chronos, who learns enough about Brainiac 5's temporal experiments to wage a battle in two eras.

XS finds herself stranded in the 20th century, unable to communicate with the locals, and against the newly repowered Chronos. The Legion in the 30th century find themselves pitted against the same foe, travelled from after his encounter with XS.
name: 2-Timer

description:
Can Gilad get the rogue trader Tully and his bank's worth of stolen gold away from the genetically modified Nazi werewolves of Fenris? Or will the stolen funds find their way into the purse of a beautiful traitor to their right wing cause?

1995 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".
name: Ill Gotten Gains
The Human Factor - Part II

description: Turok is meeting his old enemies and his old friends. The only problem is that he can't figure out how and why these meetings are happening.
name: Tree Of Life, Land Of Shadows

description: Financial woes force single mother Phyllis to work on Christmas Eve. Her daughter Nadine sneaks out, leaving little Greggy alone to await Santa. Spawn, scuffling on the roof with robbers, sounds like Santa to Greggy, then a thug drops a fat wad of cash on the fire escape. The windfall allows the family to forget about day to day worries and appreciate their many blessings.
name: Noel

description:
Overview

Hellboy's back in action with the Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense, in a full-scale mission to hunt the legendary nobleman vampire, Vladimir Giurescu, who is woken by the same newly defrosted Nazis seen in Hellboy: Seed of Destruction. The Bureau is walking into the biggest disaster in its fifty-year history! Also in this five-issue series, Mike Mignola and Dark Horse are proud to introduce the newest mysterymen on the block, Gary Gianni's (Shadow: Hell's Heatwave) MonsterMen in "Silent as the Grave"!
name: Chapter One

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description: From the cataclysmic events of ZERO HOUR and following his appearance in Superman (1987) #95, it's the return of the Atom...a reborn hero with no clues to his past, and an unwritten future! Now as the rejuvenated Ray Palmer searches for the truth of who and what he is, dark forces gather to steal a vital link to the Atom's past.
name: Critical Mass

description:
Chapter Titles

  • Chapter One: The Executioner's Song
  • Chapter Two: Church and State
  • Chapter Three: Vow of the Bat
name: Executioner

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight Annual

name: The Night Belongs To Sarah; ...

description:
On a planet in the distant future, the Shade tells a group of children two tales of times past in this over-sized issue. First up is the story behind a long-forgotten cosmic Starman who sacrifices everything to save his people. Then a tale of heroism featuring Ted Knight, the Golden Age Starman.

A Legends of the Dead Earth Annual - "Earth is dead. Those who once might have called it home are long scattered to the endless stars. But in that scattering, on a thousand different worlds, by a thousand different ways... Earth's greatest legends live on."

On another world, The Shade spins a pair of Tales of Times and Starmen Past, Prince Gavin and Ted Knight for eager listening children.
name: Legends of the Dead Earth
Book One

description: A mini-series set in the world of OZ, the popular Caliber Comic series based on the Wizard of Oz books by Frank L. Baum, as it concentrates on Scarecrow and his tattered lover, Scraps. Set in the days when Oz was controlled by the Nome King and when the Scarecrow was under the evil spell of the Nome King amulet, Scraps must decide which side to ultimately join - Scarecrow or the Freedom Fighters. This series is about the ill-fated love between Scraps the Patchwork Girl, and the Evil King Scarecrow. Although she is one of the Freedom Fighters of Oz, she cannot bear to hear their plans for her beloved's demise. Thus she steals the Freedom Fighter's secret weapon and runs away into the night!

Overview

MOM#2 Special color section issue!!! More vintage Golden Age treasures focusing on those masked good guys in this big second issue. It leads off with a spectacular Commando Yank story, (In COLOR!!) "Riddle Of The Arctic" by Dan (Flash Gordon ) Barry, from a 1948 issue of Wow Comics. Mort Meskin and Jerry Robinson provide a stunning adventure of Nedor/Standard Comics star, The Fighting Yank, "The Crossroads Of Crime", fromFighting Yank #25, 1948. The Black Terror is back, this time illustrated by Ruben (Tarzan) Moreira, as seen in Black Terror #25, December, 1948; The Ghost Rider suffers "The Return Of Magico", drawn by Dick Ayers (with Ernie Bache) from Redmask #48, published by M. E. in 1954; The Phantom Lady breaks up a "Ringside Racket", from the Ajax #1 issue, 1954, and finally Sterling Comics' Captain Flash (In COLOR!!!) takes on "The Beast From 1,000,000 BC", drawn by Mike Sekowsky for Captain Flash #3, May of 1955. All this plus the text feature, "The Story Behind The Cover", written by Roy (Conan The Barbarian) Thomas. Where else could you get all this (printed razor-sharp on 50lb white offset paper, no less ) for only $6.95? Color cover by Brad Gorby and Mark Heike, interiors are color and black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.
name: Riddle of the Arctic
The Quick, The Wicked And The Damned; ...

description: The Legends of the Dead Earth Annuals continue. In a far-flung future, the newest in the long line of Azraels must battle against twisted new incarnations of Two-Face, the Joker and the mysterious Bat King. But the young Angel of Vengeance soon discovers the Bat King has a horrifying link to his own past!
name: Night's Fall

description: The Legends of the Dead Earth Annuals continue. Two storytellers challenge each other to tell the true legend of Aquaman: in one, a king named Aquaman on a desert world doles out water by royal decree; in the other, a dying planet's seas are terrorized by a floating city called Poseidonis, ruled by Aquaman. Which is true? Which is false? And what is the secret of the storytellers themselves?
name: Legends of the Dead Earth
Book Two

description: Discovering their betrayal by Patchwork Girl, the Freedom Fighters launch a guerilla assault upon the Scarecrow's fortress barn. They unfortunately discover that the Scarecrow has built an army of his own through the magic of Magician Pipt. An army of straw golems stands between Scarecrow and the Freedom Fighters, with Scraps also caught in the middle.

name: E.L.F.s

description:
Overview

MOM#3 Special ROBOT issue! The sexy and voluptuous Phantom Lady takes on the "Case Of The Robbing Robots", from Fox Features' Phantom Lady #22, February, 1949- as drawn by that great EC Comics artist, Jack Kamen. Bob Powell launches Magazine Enterprises' Avenger against "The Robot Robber!" wherin a criminal forces a scientist to use his incredible automaton to commit crimes in this tale initially printed in The Avenger #3, June-July, 1955. Gigantic mechanical remote controlled spiders snare airliners in their "Sky Web!" until the phenomenal Captain Flash applies his atomic power to crushing the robot army, as seen in this 1955 Sterling Comics thriller by Mike Sekowsky, and Dan Barry puts Commando Yank against "The Bat Wings Of Doom", an eerie tale from WWII where Japanese agents employ vampires in this piece from a 1940's issue of Wow. Mort Meskin goes solo on the art chores when Golden Lad must face "The Menace Of The Minstral", from the Spark Publication's Golden Lad #4, April of 1946, and The Ghost Rider meets "He Who Laughs" by Carl Memley and Dick Ayers, straight out of M. E.'s Redmask #50, 1955. And Roy Thomas, who revived countless Golden Age characters at Marvel and DC, writes retro "history" teaming up Black Terror, Phantom Lady, Commando Yank and Captain Flash in the exciting "Story Behind The Cover" feature continued from MOM#2. Color cover by Dick Ayers, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.
name: The Robot Robber
Book Three

description: Will Scraps, the Patchwork Girl, finally do what's right for the land of Oz, and betray her own beloved to the Freedom Fighters? Scarecrow's straw golem army outnumber the Freedom Fighters on the field of battle and they can only hope to flee with their lives. But before that happens they witness the birth of the Scarecrow's SON! The exciting conclusion to the Romance in Rags mini series story.

Darrian has donned Mikal's armor and uses his sword to hunt down the demons he meets in New York, slaying them without mercy. A particularly nasty kick from a foe rakes his side and while tending to the wound is knocked senseless by an angel.

Recovering himself he dispatches all three of his assailants. As he walks back to collect his sword and the halo he sees a vision of Dawn in the form of a golden angel/demon form with 4 wings and horns.

At a local bar Jaynis is drowning his sorrows as Darrian enters and down a bottle of vodka. Jaynis bemoans Adelle's same act of unfaithfulness to Darrian when he notices the halo and wants to hold it. Darrian over reacts and shoves his old friend so hard he falls and breaks a horn off his beloved helm. Realizing Jaynis' rage Darrian floors him with a single punch.

Leaving the bar Darrian roams the cities empty streets seemingly cursing the halo. He passes a store front called Goddess, failing to notice Dawn is one of the mannequins inside. She looks sadly at him as he descends into a deserted subway station.
name: The Gauntlet
Book Four

description:
"The Value of I" When Taa of the planet Zilliph is chosen to wield the political system of his home world is altered dramatically.

"Nobler in the Mind" wounded in battle, the Green Lantern El'Qa Sqa Zreenah lands on a planet where the only resident "without fear" makes for an unusual replacement.
name: The Value of I / Nobler in the Mind

description:
Darrian is asleep on the subway train and is shaken awake. His instincts make him lash out with his sword, narrowly missing a cowering Adelle. She chats with him trying to reconcile their relationship while bringing up examples of her infidelity and even getting Darrian's name wrong. She fails to notice the halo he carries at all. She realizes it is hopeless and leaves the car only to be captured by a demon holding 3 halos.

The demon demands the halo in exchange for Adelle's life. Darrian refuses and instead attacks with his sword. The Demon turns on Adelle and as it slays her it is in turn slayed by Darrian. Darrian holds her as she dies.

He walks to the surface and calls down the angels who berate him for his angel killing. Demons arrive and the two armies form either side of Darrian, they don't even notice Darrian move to one side as their blood lust takes over and the two groups clash in bloody battle.

Suddenly a massive warrior appears head and shoulders over them all. An eyeless skull with twisting rams horns and massive single sided axe in hand it sweeps devastation through the ranks of angel and demon alike. Through the carnage the being strides up to Darrian and stares with light-filled eye sockets into his eyes.

The words "You killed them all" bring Darrian back to reality and a tear-less Dawn is there telling him he is stronger than them all, that was his reflection, that he is the horned god. He shakes her and her three tears run and form on her cheek.

She tells him they have lived like this before and she has been guiding him to this moment. They embrace and kiss.
name: Everybody Dies

description: "Silent Running," part of the Legends of the Dead Earth series, tells the tale of two brothers, Tristan and Bryan, gifted by the gods! Brother vs Brother, who will win in this post-apocolyptic tale?
name: Silent Running

description: As Captain Atom quantum jumps through time, he is pulled out of the Quantum Field and into the distant future of Warworld by an alternate version of Maxima to help her and that world's Blue Beetle to defeat the Alliance, an evil version of the Justice League International led by Lord Havok (with Max Lord's brain uploaded into his body) and with all of the same heroes from Captain Atom's timeline.
name: The Alliance

description: Mombi banishes the attacking Freedom Fighters to Earth where they encounter death in the form of traffic, overhead power lines, gun-happy policemen, street gangs, helicopters and tanks! Their only hope of salvation comes in the form of the Earth dog, Max. And a volcano mysteriously appears and erupts in the middle of a once-quiet meadow to the south! Based on the Wonderful Wizard of Oz books.
name: What On Earth?

description: The Winged Monkeys finally see the need in helping the Freedom Fighters, but then become pawns of the Nome King when he reveals he has the missing Monkey Cap which magically controls their allegiance. In a great finale battle, all of the players from the previous issues meet to decide the fate of Oz, once and for all! Based on the Wonderful Wizard of Oz books.
name: Battle Royale

description: A new evil is afoot in the southern lands of Oz as Goblins and Quadlings form an unholy alliance, all through the manipulations of the mysterious Shaman. Based on the Wonderful Wizard of Oz books.
name: Victory?

description: While there is celebration in Oz as news of the Nome King's defeat spreads through the land, Queen Ozma is faced with the daunting task of rebuilding her war-torn country. The Wizard, returned from his banishment to Earth, grants Kevin, Peter and Mary's request to go back to Earth. Meanwhile, the Shaman introduces the source of his mysterious power...the Wickedest Witch of Oz! Based on the Wonderful Wizard of Oz books.
name: New World Order

description:
Amber Ombi struggles to build the All-Ozzian Army in a land which has never before felt the need for a large military presence. The Wizard grows concerned about the sudden appearance of the southern volcano. Dorothy, who lost ten years of her life to the Nome King's spell, decides to search Oz for the fabled Fountain of Youth in an attempt to return to her twelve-year-old self. And an army of magically-enhanced Goblins rages through Winkieland, as the threat of the Wickedest Witch grows. Based on the classic Wonderful Wizard of Oz books.

This issue also features The Black Bombers story "The Black Star Strikes" by Ron Fortier, Christopher A. Jones and Gary Kato.
name: Peace Be So Fragile

description: The newly-independent Quadlings set out to destroy the Lion and the forest he ruled as an Evil King, to avenge the crimes Lion inflicted upon them during those dark days. Meanwhile, Dorothy and her childhood friends Trot and Betsy Bobbin, along with Scarecrow, Tin Man and Hungry Tiger, set out for Good Witch Glinda's castle to the north in search of clues to the whereabouts of the Fountain of Youth. Based on the Wonderful Wizard of Oz books.
name: Quadling Quandary

description:
Overview

The past is seemingly catching up with everyone this issue as old-timer Harry Diamond tracks down Rad to serve her with divorce papers, General Strock is called on the carpet for breach of protocol by her superior officer -who happens to be her Dad, and that ol' paranormal maker, Dr. Lieber is back, with a new hybrid- clones grown from the DNA of Rurian bodies, enhanced by V-formula super-vitamins. He calls them Furies- and they just might be the deadliest female fighting machines this planet has ever seen. And when their initial sudden, swift and deadly attack has Rad all but defeated, who comes to her aid? Out of the past, it's Mark Benton, The Terrorist. "Terror Times Two" is written and drawn by Brad Gorby, with inks by Mark Heike. Guest starring Tom Kelly and David Burke. Color cover by Brad Gorby , interiors are black and white with graytones. Standard comic book format.
name: Terror Times Two

description: The Goddess discovers her secret; she's the personification of Earth! This isn't the end...as there's still the homicidal London officer ... and the homicidal military man, both willing to kill whatever gets between them and her.
name: Mine Eyes Have Seen the Glory

deck: Fatal attraction, or dark epiphany... John Constantine will embrace his fate with open arms
description:
The Horrorist brings her cold touch of horror home to the heartland of America, moving inexorably closer to her inevitable encounter with the dark intensity of a Hellblazer's obsession.

John Constantine waits for her in Texas, caught between terror and anticipation - dreading her arrival, wanting nothing more.
name: "Antarctica" - Part Two

description: Having escaped the oppressive confines of their prison, Uncle Pencil and Nickel Pepper venture out into a world that proves to be as cold and cruel as their old home. Navigating a harrowing landscape of gutted, skeletal factories, the bloated carcasses of cruise ships, and hostile beer-swilling rednecks, the pair continues the search for the legendary Aluminum Tower.
name: Damn Your Hands

description:
In order to unseat violent fundamentalists in the central asian republic of Djurkistan, Gilad must team up with a team of multi-national commandos known only as The Force! Their mission: make the people of this remote nation believe that Gilad Anni-Padda is the the Ma'ah Bishmah, the messenger returned from God!

1996 books with a UPC code may exist as "Newsstand Sales" in addition to "Direct Sales".

1st appearance:

- The Force
name: Voices Of God
Street Smarrts

description:
1st appearance:
- BlackStar
name: Black Star

description: While exploring the Lost Land, Turok and company discover a mysterious temple which leads them to a lost Nazi civilization occupied by Nazi women.
name: Island Of Nazi Women - Part 1

description: The oldest and freshest anthology series in the comics business serves up another heaping helping of sophistication and diversity. The tales range from the supernatural to the absurd to existential to nitty-gritty crime fiction. The creators have prior credits that span the range of modern comics as well, from Ghost to Harlan Ellison's Dream Corridor to Star Wars: Dark Lords of the Sith. Paul Pope, alternative comics genius, continues "The One Trick Rip-Off," a stylish, comics noirstrip set in a near-future Los Angeles and focusing on a small group of thieves called the One Tricks. In "Cal Hairball," Steve Niles concludes his 4-part serial about Cal MacDonald, a paranormal investigator whose search for a murderer leads him into out onto a busy highway for a climactic confrontation with a werewolf. Scott Musgrove and Darick Chamberlin's "The Pink Tornado" is the world's first stillborn superhero. In this last of 3 parts, he goes up against his arch-nemesis, Dr. Canada, the Provincial Man, a man with eerily detachable body parts. "That's Mr. Painter to You" concludes Stan Shaw's existential tale of a disaffected artiste named Alan Bland -- a coffee addict and tuba aficionado -- who becomes obsessed with an old painting found in his parents' home. Dark Horse Presents is the bastion of postmodern comics, 105 issues strong. Find out why readers around the world keep coming back for more, month after month. Kitsch, comedy, and noir. If you want any more than that, you're just getting greedy.

Overview

Dead men may tell no tales, but they also don't like anyone to mess with their gold! Indy's adrift with a band of brigands on the treacherous Sargasso Sea, the graveyard of lost ships. The still waters are an archaeologist's dream, but the treasures of the Sargasso have already been claimed by legendary protectors, restless spirits who just might turn out to be more than legends after all!
name: Chapter Two: Sea of Troubles!

volume.name: Indiana Jones and the Sargasso Pirates

description: Lord Kiyoshi is a wakadanna, a young master. His rule began when his father, overlord of the Shirohoshi clan, met with an untimely death. Unproven to his people, Kiyoshi now endeavors to earn the loyalty of his people by recovering the clan's lost treasures. But his is not merely a mission of tracking, for he is not the only one in search of the Shirohoshi fortunes. Cut-throat space pirates and shape-changing aliens will spill blood for the ancient bounty, and the success of the quest and the safety of Lord Kiyoshi may come down to the courage of a single person: Space Usagi.
name: Warrior Part 1

description: Tarzan of the Apes has fought every manner of man and beast. He has seen every kind of jungle -- from the darkest rain forests of Africa to the concrete jungle of New York -- and faced every kind of horror those diverse landscapes have to offer. But nothing has prepared him for the savage creatures that now surround him, when the Lord of the Jungle finds himself mysteriously transported to the planet Mars!
name: Red Awakenings

description:
With Batman immersed in other crises in Gotham City, Azrael breaks away from Alfred, Lilhy and Brian to embark upon his own search for Shondra Kinsolving. In a deserted zoo, he confronts the two psychopathic kidnappers while time runs out for Shondra!

A ransom was set for Shondra Kinsolving. Azrael followed up, flattened the kidnappers and got her to safety.
name: Angel Rising Part Two

description:
Batman decides to spend a day stopping every crime in Gotham City--but can the Dark Knight handle it all or will overexertion take too much of a toll?

Batman returned to the cave after a rough and busy night. He and Alfred worked out some bugs in the new car and he went back out. Robin bailed him out when he was outmatched by a group which appeared to be the False Face Society.
name: Constant Whitewater

description: A Legends of the Dark Knight story where something of Bruce Wayne's childhood is stolen. As Batman he hunts for it back.
name: Favorite Things

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
'Playgrounds' Epilogue. Drawn into a book of twisted fairy tales, Tim, Molly and Mr. Wrong must play the roles Barbatos has written for them if they're to reach the end of their ordeal alive.

Tim, Molly, Sir Timothy (in the shape of a dragon), and Barbatos are in another of the strange storybooks that Molly and Tim were forced to read earlier. Barbatos is attempting to control the storyline.

Tim finds himself lost in a forest, and temporarily turns into a knight. He knows he is being manipulated by Barbatos, especially when a transparently fake owl, meant to look like his late familiar, Yo-yo, shows up. Tim plays along but the owl steals his glasses.

Sir Timothy the Dragon and Molly are stuck in a weird metal cave with a hoard of treasure. Sir Timothy is happy to be with Molly, but she (not knowing his identity) does not feel the same. Finally he persuades her to dress up like a princess, and explains that he had been growing Mollys for years. When she puts on the dress, her personality transforms into a haughty princess as well, and she starts being dismissive of the dragon.

Tim finds the cliff they're on, and at first seems to see Molly being threatened by the dragon. However, Tim easily realizes that they are just more of Barbatos's puppets, and magically creates a giant metal knight to knock them aside and go after the demon.

He finally catches Barbatos, but realizes that Molly is now trapped under the collapsed mountain. Only Sir Timothy holds up the ceiling protecting her. Molly snaps out of it when the dragon finally tells her his true identity: a future Tim Hunter, who has lived a life he is not proud of. He makes Molly promise to take steps to make sure young Tim doesn't turn out like him.

Outside, young Tim doesn't know how to get Molly out, but then his adult self blows a hole in the scrap with his dragon breath. Molly escapes, but Sir Timothy dies due to the effort, and Molly feels sad for him as he does. Molly fulfills her promise to the dragon, and makes young Tim swear by his name to never deal with demons--which is how Sir Timothy started down his dark path. She doesn't, however, tell him who the dragon was.

She and Tim leave the story, with Barbatos still stuck there.
name: Playgrounds, Epilogue: The Knight, The Dragon & The Maiden

description: Final issue. Damage is taken over by an evil, sentient metavirus and goes on a destructive rampage that threatens to leave all of Miami in ruins! The stakes are made even higher as the possessed Damage is forced to push a nuclear reactor toward meltdown. The only thing that can stop him is Iron Munro...but their battle may shatter the entire Eastern seaboard!
name: Big Bang

description: As Monarch's true scheme is revealed, Captain Atom discovers his true origin and Booster Gold's condition takes a turn for the worse!
name: Kings Healing

description: "Dead Heat! - Second Lap: A Swiftly Tilting Planet." Max is missing, and Wally and the other super speedsters investigate. Includes the origin of Savitar, the Speed Force-channeling villain and self-proclaimed "God of Motion." To be continued in Impulse #10, which is part three of Dead Heat.
name: Dead Heat Part 2 of 6

description: Donna Troy brings her boss, former Green Lantern John Stewart, to meet her new boyfriend, Green Lantern Kyle Rayner. But things turn bad when Donna finds Kyle in a precarious situation with another woman. And things go from bad to worse when a deadly force follows Stewart to Earth.
name: Changes for Green Lantern
